1. Project Title
Student Attendance Tracker System

2. Objective
To develop a console-based application that records, updates, and analyzes student attendance for multiple subjects using efficient data structures.

3. Data Structures Used
Structure (struct) – to store student details (roll no, name, attendance per subject)

Array of Structures – to manage multiple students

Functions – modular programming approach

4. Features Implemented
Add new student

Mark attendance (Present/Absent)

View attendance percentage

Generate class-wise attendance report

Search student by roll number

List students with low attendance (<75%)

5. Technologies
Language: C

Compiler: GCC / Turbo C / Online C compiler

Platform: Windows/Linux
How to Run the Code
Copy the code into a file named attendance_tracker.c

Compile using GCC:

bash
gcc attendance_tracker.c -o attendance
Run:

bash
./attendance
(On Windows: attendance.exe)

